    "Lastly, Green IT Consultant P1 explained that there was no extra budget provided by the company to actually focus on mitigating the negative environmental impact of AI, which limited their options.",
    "C. Impact of EU Regulations on AI Sustainability (RQ3)With the last theme, we studied how the related EU regulations, namely the AI Act and the CSRD, influence companies decision-making around AI sustainability.",
    "Since the CSRD is based on company size, it did not apply to interviewees from companies smaller than 500 employees.",
    "Table IV provides an overview of all created labels.TABLE IV INFLUENCE OF REGULATIONS: SUBTHEMES AND LABELS (RQ3) Subtheme Label Impact of EU AI Act None [P1, P2, P3, P4, P5, P6, P8, P9, P10, P11] Considering [P7] Impact of CSRD Complied [P3, P4, P6, P9, P10, P11] Not Applicable [P2, P5, P7, P8] None [P1]Impact of EU AI Act: Regarding the AI Act, 10 participants were either unfamiliar with it or had not taken any specific measures to comply with it (P1, P2, P3, P4, P5, P6, P8, P9, P10, P11).",
    "All these participants expressed how the AI Act did not (yet) have any noticeable effect on how AI was used in their companies."
